label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ocular adnexal lymphoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Involvement of lymph nodes not assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: No evidence of lymph node involvement. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Malignant Extragonadal Nongerminomatous Germ Cell Tumor

value.value: A malignant nongerminomatous germ cell tumor that develops as a primary tumor in an anatomic site other than the testis or ovary.

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Involvement of ipsilateral regional lymph nodes.  Note: The regional lymph nodes include preauricular (parotid), submandibular, and cervical. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pN2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Involvement of contralateral or bilateral regional lymph nodes.  Note: The regional lymph nodes include preauricular (parotid), submandibular, and cervical. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pN3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Involvement of peripheral lymph nodes not draining ocular adnexal region. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pN4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Involvement of central lymph nodes. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ocular adnexal lymphoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for ocular adnexal lymphoma. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Noncontiguous involvement of tissues or organs external to the ocular adnexa (e.g., parotid gland, submandibular gland, lung, liver, spleen, kidney, breast, etc.). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lymphomatous involvement of the bone marrow. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma pM1c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Both M1a and M1b involvement. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of ocular adnexal lymphoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of ocular adnexal lymphoma, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Stage I Extragonadal Non-Seminomatous Germ Cell Tumor
Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Ocular adnexal lymphoma with no evidence of involvement of other extranodal sites. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma cM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Noncontiguous involvement of tissues or organs external to the ocular adnexa (e.g., parotid gland, submandibular gland, lung, liver, spleen, kidney, breast, etc.). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma cM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lymphomatous involvement of the bone marrow. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ocular Adnexal Lymphoma cM1c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Both M1a and M1b involvement. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thoracic Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of thoracic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  This classification is used for lung cancer and pleural mesothelioma.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  This classification is used for both non-small cell and small cell lung carcinomas and for carcinoid tumors of the lung.  Sarcomas and other rare tumors of the lung are not included. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The pathologic classification uses the evidence acquired before treatment, supplemented or modified by the additional evidence acquired during and after surgery, particularly from pathologic examination. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Lung Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with a tumor size of 3 cm or less in greatest dimension, surrounded by lung or visceral pleura and without bronchoscopic evidence of invasion more proximal than the lobar bronchus (i.e., not in the main bronchus). The uncommon superficial tumor of any size with its invasive component limited to the bronchial wall, which may extend proximal to the main bronchus, is also classified as T1a. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pT1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with a tumor size of 2 cm or less in greatest dimension, surrounded by lung or visceral pleura and without bronchoscopic evidence of invasion more proximal than the lobar bronchus (i.e., not in the main bronchus). The uncommon superficial tumor of any size with its invasive component limited to the bronchial wall, which may extend proximal to the main bronchus, is also classified as T1a. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage II Extragonadal Non-Seminomatous Germ Cell Tumor
Lung Cancer pT1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with a tumor size more than 2 cm but 3 cm or less in greatest dimension, surrounded by lung or visceral pleura and without bronchoscopic evidence of invasion more proximal than the lobar bronchus (i.e., not in the main bronchus). The uncommon superficial tumor of any size with its invasive component limited to the bronchial wall, which may extend proximal to the main bronchus, is also classified as T1a. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with a tumor size more than 3 cm but 7 cm or less or tumor with any of the following features (T2 tumors with these features are classified T2a if 5 cm or less): Involves main bronchus, 2 cm or more distal to the carina; Invades visceral pleura (PL1 or PL2); Associated with atelectasis or obstructive pneumonitis that extends to the hilar region but does not involve the entire lung.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pT2a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with a tumor size more than 3 cm but 5 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pT2b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with a tumor size more than 5 cm but 7 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with a tumor size more than 7 cm or one that directly invades any of the following: parietal pleural (PL3) chest wall (including superior sulcus tumors), diaphragm, phrenic nerve, mediastinal pleura, parietal pericardium; or tumor in the main bronchus (less than 2 cm distal to the carina but without involvement of the carina); or associated atelectasis or obstructive pneumonitis of the entire lung or separate tumor nodule(s) in the same lobe. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with a tumor of any size that invades any of the following: mediastinum, heart, great vessels, trachea, recurrent laryngeal nerve, esophagus, vertebral body, carina, and separate tumor nodule(s) in a different ipsilateral lobe. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Lung Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with metastasis in ipsilateral peribronchial and/or ipsilateral hilar lymph nodes and intrapulmonary lymph nodes, including involvement by direct extension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for lung cancer. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage III Extragonadal Non-Seminomatous Germ Cell Tumor
Lung Cancer pM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with separate tumor nodule(s) in a contralateral lobe; tumor with pleural nodules or malignant pleural (or pericardial) effusion.  Most pleural (and pericardial) effusions with lung cancer are due to tumor.  In a few patients, however, multiple cytopathologic examinations of pleural (or pericardial) fluid) are negative for tumor, and the fluid is nonbloody and is not an exudate.  Where these elements and clinical judgment dictate that the effusion is not related to the tumor, the effusion should be excluded as a staging element and the patient should be classified as M0. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer pM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The clinical classification is based on the evidence acquired before treatment, including physical examination, imaging studies, laboratory tests, and staging procedures such as bronchoscopy or esophagoscopy with ultrasound directed biopsies, mediastinoscopy, mediastinotomy, thoracentesis, and thoracoscopy as well as exploratory thoracotomy.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Lung Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer cM1a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Lung cancer with separate tumor nodule(s) in a contralateral lobe; tumor with pleural nodules or malignant pleural (or pericardial) effusion.  Most pleural (and pericardial) effusions with lung cancer are due to tumor.  In a few patients, however, multiple cytopathologic examinations of pleural (or pericardial) fluid) are negative for tumor, and the fluid is nonbloody and is not an exudate.  Where these elements and clinical judgment dictate that the effusion is not related to the tumor, the effusion should be excluded as a staging element and the patient should be classified as M0. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Lung Cancer cM1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage I Lung Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage I includes: IA: (T1a, N0, M0); (T1b, N0, M0) and IB: (T2a, N0, M0).  T1a: Lung cancer with a tumor size of 2 cm or less n greatest dimension, surrounded by lung or visceral pleura and without bronchoscopic evidence of invasion more proximal than the lobar bronchus (i.e., not in the main bronchus). The uncommon superficial tumor of any size with its invasive component limited to the bronchial wall, which may extend proximal to the main bronchus, is also classified as T1a.  T1b: Lung cancer with a tumor size more than 2 cm but 3 cm or less in greatest dimension, surrounded by lung or visceral pleura and without bronchoscopic evidence of invasion more proximal than the lobar bronchus (i.e., not in the main bronchus).  T2a: Lung cancer with a tumor size more than 3 cm but 5 cm or less in greatest dimension.  N0: No regional lymph metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage II Lung Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage II includes: IIA (T2b, N0, M0); (T1a, N1, M0); (T1b, N1, M0); (T2a, N1, M0) and IIB (T2b, N1, M0); (T3, N0, M0).  T2b: Lung cancer with a tumor size more than 5 cm but 7 cm or less in greatest dimension.  T1a: Lung cancer with a tumor size of 2 cm or less in greatest dimension, surrounded by lung or visceral pleura and without bronchoscopic evidence of invasion more proximal than the lobar bronchus (i.e., not in the main bronchus). The uncommon superficial tumor of any size with its invasive component limited to the bronchial wall, which may extend proximal to the main bronchus, is also classified as T1a.  T1b: Lung cancer with a tumor size more than 2 cm but 3 cm or less in greatest dimension, surrounded by lung or visceral pleura and without bronchoscopic evidence of invasion more proximal than the lobar bronchus (i.e., not in the main bronchus).  T2a: Lung cancer with a tumor size more than 3 cm but 5 cm or less in greatest dimension.  T3: Lung cancer with a tumor size more than 7 cm or one that directly invades any of the following: parietal pleural (PL3) chest wall (including superior sulcus tumors), diaphragm, phrenic nerve, mediastinal pleura, parietal pericardium; or tumor in the main bronchus (less than 2 cm distal to the carina but without involvement of the carina); or associated atelectasis or obstructive pneumonitis of the entire lung or separate tumor nodule(s) in the same lobe. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  N1: Lung cancer with metastasis in ipsilateral peribronchial and/or ipsilateral hilar lymph nodes and intrapulmonary lymph nodes, including involvement by direct extension. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Extragonadal Non-Seminomatous Germ Cell Tumor
Stage III Lung Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage III includes: IIIA (T1a, N2, M0); (T1b, N2, M0); (T2a, N2, M0); (T2b, N2, M0); (T3, N1, M0); (T3, N2, M0); (T4, N0, M0); (T4, N1, M0) and IIIB (T1a, N3, M0); (T1b, N3, M0); (T2a, N3, M0); (T2b, N3, M0); (T3, N3, M0); (T4, N2, M0); (T4, N3, M0).  T4: Lung cancer with a tumor of any size that invades any of the following: mediastinum, heart, great vessels, trachea, recurrent laryngeal nerve, esophagus, vertebral body, carina, and separate tumor nodule(s) in a different ipsilateral lobe.  N1: Lung cancer with metastasis in ipsilateral peribronchial and/or ipsilateral hilar lymph nodes and intrapulmonary lymph nodes, including involvement by direct extension.  N2: Lung cancer with metastasis to ipsilateral mediastinal and/or subcarinal lymph nodes.  N3: Lung cancer with metastasis to contralateral mediastinal, contralateral hilar, ipsilateral or contralateral scalene, or supraclavicular lymph nodes.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Lung Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IV includes: (Any T, Any N, M1a); (Any T, Any N, M1b).  M1a: Lung cancer with separate tumor nodule(s) in a contralateral lobe; tumor with pleural nodules or malignant pleural (or pericardial) effusion.  M1b: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)
